node.text: This week, on the podcast @blackfolx, online educator, content creator in the travel space and an entrepreneur Gloria Atanmo (@glographics ) joins host Brandon Kyle Goodman (@brandonkgood ) to discuss their experiences being catapulted into the forefront of anti-racism education on instagram and what it means to travel while Black. In this clip they also discuss they're feelings on white people they don't know calling them "sis". Link in stories for full episode: "Stay True to Your Shape".

node.title: White people, I am not your "sis"

This week on the @blackfolx podcast, BKG (@brandonkgood ) welcomes actor and writer Clark Moore (@mrclarkmoore ). They talk about the most influential Black men in thier lives and how often times, older generations of Black folx passed down respectability politics as a way to protect the next generation from racism. In this clip they also discuss racism in the work place.
For the full episode link in stories!
